investments and managed accounts, and currently has $30 billion in invested and committed Real Estate and Infrastructure assets and capital. Our 300-person team is based in 22 offices globally.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Job Purpose/Background:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>This London based role will work across the BlackRock Real Assets global platform with particular focus and partnership with BlackRockâs European Real Estate Funds. The VP, Product Strategy will create and be responsible for the execution of a Product Plan for a series of BlackRock Real Estate funds. The role requires deep subject matter expertise, the ability to drive a schedule and the ability to work in a team based environment in close co-operation with many of BlackRockâs teams including Portfolio Management, Global Client Relationship Management, Global Consultant Relations, Investor Relations, Finance, Operations and the management of BlackRockâs Alternatives business.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Key Responsibilities:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ The role will be responsible for further developing BlackRockâs European Real Estate product suite, with initial emphasize of the launch of BlackRockâs next generation of EU products; particular focus items will include</p><p>+ Investment Strategy development and articulation, including thought leadership on the market environment, the investment opportunity and the competitive environment</p><p>+ Product planning &amp; development, including leading the preparation and project management of a product development lifecycle</p><p>+ Product Launch management, including driving go-to-market planning and distribution preparation</p><p>+ Fundraising and Marketing execution, partnering with BlackRockâs various distribution and Portfolio Management teams in preparing and presenting the investment opportunity to prospective clients, team schedule management, leading response to RFPs and client diligence</p><p>+ Marketing and Communications to support brand and product development</p><p>+ Measurement, Tracking and Reporting, development and management of client pipelines</p><p>+ Ongoing client mandate &amp; relationship support</p><p>+ The VP, Product Strategy will be key resource for market and competitive intelligence and will take a leadership role in the development and design of future products and strategies to meet global client needs.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Skills/Qualifications:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Deep real estate market knowledge, with a focus on European markets</p><p>+ Qualitative and quantitative presentation and communication skills are essential to this role, particularly the ability to distil complex structural and financial issues into plain language.</p><p>+ Previous relevant experience working within business development, Investment Research, Investor Relations in Consulting, Capital Markets. Real Estate, Private Equity or Private Credit.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Strong capability with project based work and ability to multi-task and work in a fast paced environment.</p><p>+ Ability to operate as part of an internationally distributed team.</p><p>+ Fluency in English essential, European languages preferred</p><p>+ Strong analytical and conceptual skills with the ability to present detailed financial concepts in a simple, clear and concise fashion. Full proficiency in Word, Excel and Power Point.Masterâs degree preferred or undergraduate degree or equivalent with intended progression to CFA or CAIA</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Job Function:** _Product Management_</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Organization:** _Inv-Alt-Real Assets_</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Title:** _BlackRock Real Assets, Product Strategy - Vice President_</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Primary Location:** _EMEA-United Kingdom-London_</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Requisition ID:** _162342_</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Job Posting:*